Raila Odinga, the ODM leader, has previously mounted serious presidential campaigns without meticulous and professional organisation. This time, the former Prime Minister’s team is planning to consolidate his front-runner status with a wave of high-profile organising, fundraising and endorsement news when he enters the race officially later this year. Raila’s presidential campaign has been burning the midnight oil, assembling powerful, well-respected professionals who will manage his presidential campaign. Apart from mobilising campaign cash, Raila’s team is tapping decades-old friendships to line up support, people with direct knowledge of his campaign strategy said